 File Permissions & Ownership
Command Description
ls -l To check file permissions.
chmod <permissions> <file-name> To change file permissions.
chown <new-username> <file-name> To change ownership of a file.
chown -R <new-username> <dir-name> To change ownership of a directory recursively.
chgrp <new-groupname> <file-name> To change the group ownership of a file.
chgrp -R <new-groupname> <dir-name> To change the group ownership of a directory
recursively
